# MQL5 Grid Hedging EA Rules

## Code Style
- Use descriptive variable names with Hungarian notation where appropriate
- Group inputs using `//--- Section Name ---//` comments
- Use enums for trade directions and cycle states
- Keep functions under 100 lines where possible

## Trading Logic
- Always validate spread before opening trades
- Check margin availability before sending orders
- Use magic numbers to identify EA trades
- Normalize lot sizes to broker specifications
- Handle partial fills and requotes gracefully

## Error Handling
- Log all trade operations with Print/PrintFormat
- Retry failed operations with appropriate delays
- Check GetLastError() after every trade operation

## File Structure
- Main EA file: GridHedge_EA.mq5
- All code in single file for easy distribution
- Well-commented sections for each logical component
